  "text": "1. (quadratic twists, j(E ) = 0, 1728) y 2 = x 3 + aH(T ) 2 x + bH(T ) 3 , where a, b = 0 and H(T ), A(T ), B(T ) are polynomials with integer coefficients. In a previous article [CITATION_1] , the author proves that the function t → W (E t ) defined by the root number on a non-isotrivial family E is never periodic (i.e. constant on a congruence class of t). More precisely, we prove that the sets W ± = {t ∈ P 1 | W (E t ) = ±1} are both infinite, which implies (under the parity conjecture) the Zariski-density of the rational points E (Q).",
